<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF-ROAD ENTHUSIASTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In "A Desert Dowry" (Dec. 16), you group off-road vehicle enthusiasts like 
myself along with illegal dumpers and land developers as those who are 
contributing to the decimation of Joshua trees in Lancaster. This is unfair to 
off-roaders, who are by and large law-abiding taxpayers who love the desert but 
who happen to actually go out and enjoy it.By comparison, illegal dumpers are 
slovens breaking the law, while powerful developers manipulate the law to their 
own ends, destroy whole areas and call it legal. Moreover, I fail to see how an 
off-roader can do any significant damage to a Joshua tree -- some of them are 
kind of big. 
</P>
<P>
 The preservation of the desert is a very important effort, and many 
off-roaders are more than willing to be a constructive part of the process. 
Unsubstantiated, off-the-cuff and prejudiced allegations are counterproductive. 
</P>
<P>
 GEORGE BINER 
</P>
<P>
 El Segundo 
</P>
</TEXT>
