because of a back injury to score 28 points in leading the Hawkeyes (9-1) over 
the Blue Devils (6-2) in the first round of the Rainbow Classic at Honolulu. 
</P>
<P>
 Settles, a sophomore forward, scored seven points and had an assist in a 13-5 
run that gave Iowa a 76-65 lead with 2:53 to play. 
</P>
<P>
 Duke got back within 76-71 on consecutive three-point baskets by freshman 
Trajan Langdon, but Iowa made five of six free throws in the final 43 seconds. 
</P>
