<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE BOWLS DAILY REPORT; COTTON; USC, TEXAS TECH BOTH HAVE THE HORSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It'll be a two-horse Cotton Bowl Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Texas Tech and USC have hoofed mascots, although Texas Tech's Two Bar Boy is 
the Red Raiders' interim mascot.Their previous steed, Double-T, hit his head 
during a game and died.  
</P>
<P>
 The Trojans' Traveler IV will be trucked to Dallas this week, and rider Tom 
Nolan will have the white Arabian dash about the Cotton Bowl every time USC 
scores.  
</P>
<P>
 Texas Tech followers went into shock at what happened during the Sept. 3 New 
Mexico game at Lubbock. Double-T's rider, Amy Smart, fell off the coal-black 
horse when her saddle cinch broke. 
</P>
<P>
 Double-T bolted, ran riderless across the end zone, then made a sudden turn to 
gallop up the stadium ramp. He ran head-first into a concrete abutment and died 
instantly.  
</P>
<P>
 Texas Tech will shop for a black quarter horse in the off-season, and will 
probably name the successor Double-T II. EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
