<P>
THE BOWLS DAILY REPORT; ORANGE; ERICKSON HAS 'NO INTEREST' IN SEAHAWKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Miami Coach Dennis Erickson, rumored to be a leading candidate for the Seattle 
Seahawks' job if Tom Flores is fired, said Tuesday he has "no interest" in 
going to the NFL. 
</P>
<P>
 "College football is what I want to do," Erickson said."I'd like to win a few 
more national championships here." 
</P>
<P>
 Monday, Erickson walked out of an interview after practice when asked about 
the Seattle situation. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Nebraska Coach Tom Osborne plans to announce Thursday whether Brook Berringer 
or Tommie Frazier will be his starting quarterback Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 "They both practiced pretty well (Tuesday)," Osborne said. "After tomorrow's 
practice, I'll talk to them. . . . and we'll probably say something the next 
day." 
</P>
<P>
 Frazier started Nebraska's first four games before being sidelined because of 
blood clots in his right leg. Berringer then took over and led the top-ranked 
Cornhuskers to eight victories in a row. 
</P>
