<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' SOCCER ROUNDUP; RICHARD'S GOAL GETS IRVINE PAST EL MODENA, 2-1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GEOFF BILAU 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After setting up her teammates for shot after shot with centering passes from 
the left wing, Irvine's Rise Richard found her Vaqueros still locked in a tie 
with El Modena Tuesday. So she took it upon herself to score the game winner. 
</P>
<P>
 Richard's goal, a high-arching lob shot from 25 yards out that was too high 
for goalkeeper Marie Dillon, gave No. 9 Irvine a 2-1 victory and moved the 
Vaqueros into the quarterfinals of the Excalibur Tournament at Foothill High. 
Irvine (10-1-1) plays No. 1 Marina in a quarterfinal game at noon today. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine controlled the ball throughout the game with aggressive play at 
midfield. Vaquero Coach Hamid Sedehi credited forwards Richard and Shannon 
Milovich with setting the pace. 
</P>
<P>
 "Shannon and Rise came on strong," he said. "They are very talented players 
with good touch on the ball." 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine scored first, early in the first half when Sarah Denson intercepted a 
pass in front of the El Modena goal and fed Katie Roda for an easy tap-in. 
</P>
<P>
 El Modena had few scoring chances in the game, but converted late in the first 
half when Kaylee Whitfield controlled a corner kick and drilled a shot into the 
upper left corner to tie the score, 1-1. 
</P>
<P>
 But Richard chipped in her unlikely game-winner midway through the second half 
and Irvine held on the rest of the way. 
</P>
<P>
 "I always take shots from right there, but I guess this one was kind of 
lucky," Richard said. GEOFF BILAU 
</P>
</TEXT>
