<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' SOCCER ROUNDUP; LOS ALAMITOS BEATS LAGUNA HILLS; SANTA MARGARITA NEXT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mike Lalond, Jeff Leitner and Toren Wallace scored for Los Alamitos in a 3-0 
victory over Laguna Hills in a first-round game in the Orange Holiday boys' 
soccer tournament Tuesday at Orange. 
</P>
<P>
 The Griffins (7-0-3), ranked fourth in Orange County, play top-ranked Santa 
Margarita at 12:30 today at Rancho Santiago College. 
</P>
<P>
 In other tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita 4, Katella 0 -- Seth George scored two goals to lead Santa 
Margarita (10-0-1). 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra 1, Estancia 1 (La Habra advances on penalty kicks) -- Miguel Zelia 
scored a goal with less than a minute left to play to tie the score for 
Estancia (3-2-2). La Habra advances to the second round, winning 3-1 on penalty 
kicks. 
</P>
<P>
 The Highlanders (4-0-2) play Orange at 10:45 a.m. today at Rancho Santiago. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 1, Trabuco Hills 1 (Orange advances on penalty kicks) -- Victor Diaz 
scored a goal with five minutes left in the game for Orange, which then won on 
penalty kicks, 4-2. 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside North 1, Foothill 1 (North advances on penalty kicks) -- Adam 
Campbell scored Foothill's only goal. North won on penalty kicks, 3-2. The 
Knights (4-2-3) play Sonora at 11:30 a.m. today at Orange. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana 1, Sonora 0 -- Juan Bolanos scored a first-half goal to lead Santa 
Ana (4-2-1). The Saints play Riverside North at 3 p.m. at Orange. 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 4, Sunny Hills 2 -- Todd Marcus scored two goals for Edison (5-1-4). 
The Chargers play Saddleback at 9 a.m. at Rancho Santiago. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 2, West Torrance 1 -- Carlos Vizcaino and Ramon Alvarado each 
scored goals for Saddleback.  
</P>
<P>
 In the Marina tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor 2, Los Angeles Ayala 1 -- Steve Kleha had 14 saves and Chris 
Wakim and Dom Fratantaro scored for Newport Harbor (8-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley 3, El Toro 0 -- Joey Vasquez had two goals and Scott Hainlen 
made four saves for second-ranked Fountain Valley (8-1), which will play Long 
Beach Wilson at 10:45 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach 4, Aliso Niguel 3 -- Freshman Aaron McAthy scored his second 
varsity goal and midfielder Robert Ramirez had three assists for the Oilers 
(4-5-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Campbell scored twice for Aliso Niguel. Byron Livingston had four saves 
for Huntington Beach, which plays South Torrance at 9 a.m. today. The Oilers 
lost to Tustin, 3-1, earlier Tuesday. 
