<P>
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL; BRUINS PLAY KENTUCKY; USC, 49ERS TANGLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WENDY WITHERSPOON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The UCLA women's basketball team will play host to Kentucky at 5 p.m. in 
Pauley Pavilion today, and USC will play host to Long Beach State at 7:30 in 
the Lyon Center to open its three-night round-robin tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA's Kisa Hughes averaged 19.7 points and a tournament-high 12.7 rebounds to 
lead the 4-3 Bruins to the final of the three-day Northern Lights tournament at 
Anchorage, Alaska, last week, where UCLA lost to 8-2 Clemson, 79-62. 
</P>
<P>
 Kentucky (3-5) is led by Stacey Reed, a guard who averages 14 points and 7.3 
rebounds a game. 
</P>
<P>
 The 21st-ranked Trojans (5-1) trail the 49ers in their all-time series, 26-13. 
Long Beach (2-3) has won seven of the last eight, but USC won the last one, two 
years ago, 101-48. 
</P>
<P>
 USC's tournament continues in the Lyon Center Thursday, when Long Beach will 
play North Carolina Charlotte (5-1) at 7:30 p.m., and concludes Friday, when 
USC plays North Carolina Charlotte at 7:30 p.m. WENDY WITHERSPOON 
