<P>
FISH REPORT: FONTANA ANGLER HAS PLENTY OF FISH TO FRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two limits by the same person on the same day? 
</P>
<P>
 Don't call the Fish and Game warden.Because Corona Lake is privately operated 
by Outdoor Safaris International, it was perfectly legal when Fred Vecht of 
Fontana caught one five-fish limit of rainbow trout, then bought another gate 
pass and went back out to his hot spot to catch another limit. 
</P>
<P>
 Vecht used green Power Bait along the west shore. Anglers are advised not to 
exceed the one-day limit on public waters. 
</P>
