1971 and became president in 1973, serving for seven years. When he stepped 
down, Federated was generating annual sales of about $7 billion. Krensky 
graduated from Boston University in 1935 and earned a law degree from the 
school. He joined the Board of Trustees in 1964. In New York City on Sunday. 
