<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: SYLMAR; LIBRARY SUPPORTERS TO HOLD BOOK SALE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Friends of the Sylmar Library will hold their first used-book sale of the 
new year Jan. 10 in the parking lot behind the library, 13059 Glenoaks Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 About five times a year, the friends put on a sale to raise money to buy new 
books and sponsor reading programs for the library, said event coordinator Pat 
Lee. 
</P>
<P>
 "They've been cutting from the budget for the last five years," Lee said.  
</P>
<P>
 She said the Friends of the Sylmar Library raise $350 per book sale, where 
used books donated from the public are sold for about 25 cents each. 
</P>
<P>
 One of the club's long-term goals is to raise enough money to find a newer and 
bigger facility for the library, Lee said. MAKI BECKER 
</P>
