COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; SADDLEBACK TO OFFER OCEAN SKILLS CLASSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sailing, navigation and SCUBA classes are being offered this spring at 
Saddleback College. 
</P>
<P>
 A 16-week sailing class that starts Jan. 20 will offer experienced sailors a 
chance to work on ocean sailing skills and supervising a crew. Students will 
also plan and carry out cruises to Santa Catalina Island and the Channel 
Islands. 
</P>
<P>
 A celestial navigation class beginning Jan. 18 will help students develop 
practical skills, plus learn how to use a sextant and chronometer to chart 
waters by the stars and sky. 
</P>
<P>
 The SCUBA class starts April 11. 
</P>
<P>
 At the end of the six-week course, students should have the skills to 
participate in open water dives necessary for certification. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 582-4541. JEFF BEAN 
</P>
