<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: FLU SHOTS AVAILABLE AT COUNTY CLINICS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By IRA E. STOLL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Flu season is already under way, but county public health officials say it is 
not too late to be immunized. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ventura County Department of Public Health suggests the shots for people 
most vulnerable to getting the flu: those over 60, those with chronic health 
problems, and young adults with heart, liver and respiratory problems, 
including asthma. 
</P>
<P>
 The shots are also available for those who have frequent contact with the 
public, such as teachers, firefighters and police officers. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura County Public Health Officer Gary M. Feldman said the flu vaccine is 
usually in short supply, but that a recent delivery has left the county with a 
surplus. 
</P>
<P>
 The cost of the shots is $5. 
</P>
<P>
 For details or to schedule an appointment, call the county public health 
clinic at 652-5918 in Ventura, 385-8652 in Oxnard or 584-5887 in Simi Valley. 
IRA E. STOLL 
</P>
</TEXT>
