<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; GIRL, 2, WHO FELL IN POOL 9 MONTHS AGO DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THAO HUA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 2-year-old who tumbled into a swimming pool earlier this year died after 
spending nine months in a coma, authorities said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Mariyam Ismail died at home in the 9900 block of Oasis Avenue on Monday, after 
months of daily prayers by her grandparents, parents, aunts and uncles. 
</P>
<P>
 The toddler fell into a back yard swimming pool March 17 while her family was 
eating lunch, her uncle, Mohammed Ismail, said. About five minutes later, the 
child's aunt, Shahen Ismail, saw her lying face down in the pool and shouted 
for help. Mariyam's father, Afzal Ismail, then jumped in after his daughter and 
tried to resuscitate her.  
</P>
<P>
 When paramedics arrived, the child still was not breathing and was taken to 
Fountain Valley Regional Hospital and Medical Center, where she regained a 
pulse but remained in a coma. After about two months in the hospital, family 
members took the comatose child home so that her mother, Salma Ismail, could 
care for her, Mohammed Ismail said. 
</P>
<P>
 Afzal and Salma Ismail have two other young children, Salama and Noman. They 
have since built a fence around the swimming pool, Mohammed Ismail said.THAO 
HUA 
</P>
</TEXT>
