</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By IRA E. STOLL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If you get a phone call from the Oxnard police asking for money, it's a fraud, 
Oxnard police said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Detective Len Newcomb said the department has recently received several 
reports from residents saying they have been called by people soliciting 
donations for the police. 
</P>
<P>
 Newcomb said the Oxnard Police Department does not engage in such phone 
solicitations. He said people should give only to recognized, legitimate 
organizations, and take the time to check out charities by asking for a name 
and call-back number before giving out any information or pledging any money 
over the phone. IRA E. STOLL 
