EAST VENTURA COUNTY: SIMI VALLEY; SINGLE SUSPECT SOUGHT IN 2 HOLDUPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By IRA E. STOLL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Simi Valley police are searching for a man who they believe was responsible 
for two robberies that occurred within an hour of each other Tuesday, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The first robbery occurred about 1:40 p.m. at the Mail Depot store, 2760 Tapo 
Canyon Road.The robber, armed with a handgun, escaped with an undetermined 
amount of cash, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The second robbery took place shortly after 2 p.m. at Popeye's Famous Fried 
Chicken & Biscuits restaurant, 1883 Erringer Road. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's the same description, the same method of operation, and it happened 
about the same time," Sgt. Mike King said. He added that police believe the 
same person was responsible for both crimes but had no suspects. 
</P>
<P>
 Police chased one suspect after the first robbery but determined he was not 
involved in the crime. 
</P>
<P>
 No shots were fired and no one was injured in either robbery, police said. IRA 
E. STOLL 
