NATION IN BRIEF; WASHINGTON STATE; OFFICER IN ABORTION DELAY CASE IS FIRED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 State Trooper Lane Jackstadt, charged with illegally detaining a couple en 
route to an abortion clinic, was fired for allegedly cheating on a promotion 
exam in 1993, a spokesman said. The case is not related to the abortion clinic 
incident. A trial date is pending for Jackstadt, who is charged with unlawful 
imprisonment and official misconduct for allegedly holding Deanna Thomas, 18, 
