<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: BANKING & FINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 T-Bill Rates Drop: Interest rates on short-term Treasury securities fell in 
auction to the lowest level in a month.The Treasury Department sold $13.0 
billion in three-month bills at an average discount rate of 5.56%, down from 
5.59% last week. An additional $13.1 billion was sold in six-month bills at an 
average discount rate of 6.24%, down from 6.30%. The three-month bill rate was 
the lowest since the bills sold for 5.44% on Nov. 28. The six-month bill rate 
was the lowest since it averaged 5.86%, also Nov. 28. The new discount rates 
understate the actual return to investors: 5.72% for three-month bills, with a 
$10,000 bill selling for $9,859.50 and 6.53% for a six-month bill selling for 
$9,684.50. 
</P>
