<P>
 FCC to Streamline Bidding for Small Firms: Auctions of mobile phone licenses 
for entrepreneurs that want in on the wireless personal communications services 
market will be put on a fast track under a new Federal Communications 
Commission plan aimed at reducing bidding complexity and speeding license 
awards. Federal regulators have set aside a block of licenses to help small 
companies compete with wealthier giants such as AT&T and the regional Bell 
telephone companies. Bidding is restricted to companies or individuals with 
less than $125 million in gross revenue and total assets of less than $500 
million. 
