</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pacific Gulf Properties Inc.: The company said Tuesday it has acquired 
Crescent Business Center, a business and industrial park in Rancho Cucamonga, 
from Transamerica Occidental Life Insurance Co. for $5 million in cash and 
notes. 
</P>
<P>
 The Crescent Business Center complex, developed in 1981, includes nine 
industrial buildings on a site of about 19 acres. Pacific Gulf said the 
complex, which now has 24 business and industrial users, is 95% occupied. 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Gulf, a real estate investment trust based in Newport Beach, owns and 
operates multifamily and industrial properties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
